\begin_layout Itemize
From this, we derive the characteristic equation 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\phi_{2}(\lambda,x_{t})}{Wr(x_{t})}-\frac{\phi_{2}(\lambda,x_{r})}{\text{Wr}(x_{r})}=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Our system of equation for the coefficients is homogeneous, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
A\begin{pmatrix}a\\
b\\
c
\end{pmatrix}=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 would be invertible, then the trivial solution 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{pmatrix}a\\
b\\
c
\end{pmatrix}=0
\]

\end_inset

would be the only solution 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The characteristic equation ensures that 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is not invertible 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
So how do we solve the system of equations?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
